<ul><li><a href="/wiki/1139" title="1139">1139</a> – <b><a href="/wiki/1139_Ganja_earthquake" title="1139 Ganja earthquake">A violent earthquake</a></b> struck the <a href="/wiki/Caucasus" title="Caucasus">Caucasus</a> near <a href="/wiki/Ganja,_Azerbaijan" title="Ganja, Azerbaijan">Ganja</a>, killing up to an estimated 300,000 people.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/1791" title="1791">1791</a> – <a href="/wiki/Wolfgang_Amadeus_Mozart" title="Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart">Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart</a>'s opera <i><b><a href="/wiki/The_Magic_Flute" title="The Magic Flute">The Magic Flute</a></b></i>, composed shortly before his death, premiered at <a href="/wiki/Theater_auf_der_Wieden" title="Theater auf der Wieden">Theater auf der Wieden</a> in <a href="/wiki/Vienna" title="Vienna">Vienna</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/1920" title="1920">1920</a> – <b><a href="/wiki/Times_Square_Theater" title="Times Square Theater">Times Square Theater</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> opened on <a href="/wiki/Broadway_theatre" title="Broadway theatre">Broadway</a> with a production of <i><a href="/wiki/The_Mirage_(play)" title="The Mirage (play)">The Mirage</a></i>, a play written by its owner, <a href="/wiki/Edgar_Selwyn" title="Edgar Selwyn">Edgar Selwyn</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/1939" title="1939">1939</a> – <a href="/wiki/NBC" title="NBC">NBC</a> broadcast the <b><a href="/wiki/1939_Waynesburg_vs._Fordham_football_game" title="1939 Waynesburg vs. Fordham football game">first televised American football game</a></b>, between the <a href="/wiki/Fordham_Rams_football" title="Fordham Rams football">Fordham Rams</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Waynesburg_University" title="Waynesburg University">Waynesburg Yellow Jackets</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/2000" title="2000">2000</a> – Twelve-year-old <b><a href="/wiki/Killing_of_Muhammad_al-Durrah" title="Killing of Muhammad al-Durrah">Muhammad al-Durrah</a></b> was shot dead in the <a href="/wiki/Gaza_Strip" title="Gaza Strip">Gaza Strip</a>; the <a href="/wiki/Israel_Defense_Forces" title="Israel Defense Forces">Israel Defense Forces</a> initially accepted responsibility but retracted it five years later.</li></ul>
